    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="839"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/130</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Danish Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Danish Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bar Harbor</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose for your inspection
                    the full-power by which His Majesty the King of Denmark was pleased to authorize
                    me to sign the treaty for the cession to the United States of the Danish West
                    India Islands.<note n="8" xml:id="d839fn8">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You will notice that the King’s signature is dated Copenhagen August 1st, 1916
                    and that, in accordance with instructions by cable from the Danish Government, I
                    had the honor of signing the treaty with you at New York on August 4th.</p>
                <p>I beg that after inspection of this document you will be so good as to return it
                    to me, to be kept with the records of this Legation.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Brun</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
